article.headline: Kennesaw State 67, Stetson 65
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- LaDaris Green scored on a buzzer-beating tip-in to lift Kennesaw State over Stetson 67-65 on Saturday night. Spencer Dixon, who had a game-winning 3-pointer with 3 seconds to go for a 69-68 Kennesaw State win just two nights prior, started the final play against Stetson bydriving down the lane. His floater with 2 seconds left bounced off the rim, but Green was there for the follow. Green tallied his fourth straight double-double with 17 points and 10 rebounds. Markeith Cummings scored 22 points and Artie Marine chipped in 12 for the Owls (8-17, 6-9 Atlantic Sun Conference). Kennesaw State was just 6 of 27 from the field in the first half to trail 32-27 at the break. The Owls improved to 50-percent shooting (14 of 28) in the second half for their third straight win. Luis Jacobo led the Hatters (7-20, 5-11) with 18 points. Corey Walden chipped in 14 points for Stetson.
